snippet.textDisplay:
Found this video cool but I do hope people don't start going instantly vegan for a short period just to lose a bit a of weight.
Chances are, like Morgan said, it's probably mostly water weight that you'll lose. Not to mention, if you change your diet drastically then your body will think its being starved so it will actually store the weight and you'll feel larger.
There's nothing wrong with going vegan, but just make sure to transition over a long period of time and it will have long-term effects!

Evolutionary biologists > “nutritionists”

Reason > false moral virtue signaling

snippet.textDisplay: The weight loss benefits of being vegan are insane! I used to limit myself to like 800 calories a day (horrible I know) as a meat eater. I lost a little weight after a few months. Since being vegan, I’ve lost 20lbs. I’ve never counted a calorie and I’ve never gained the weight back. I literally eat so much it’s horrifying. But I’ve never gone over 110lbs. And I get compliments that I look healthy!

snippet.textDisplay: I used to be a vegetarian most of my life. Then about two years ago I just started eating meat. And I never went back. I weigh less now than when I was a vegetarian. From my experience for me at least I found cutting out meat to be extreme and I found over eating meat to be extreme. There's a balance you know where you don't have to restrict things extremely in order to maintain a body shape. Just eat in moderation. Have some self-control and willpower according to your own metabolism and you'll be just fine.
